# Alpha — Paper 63: The Alpha Theorem

**The necessary ontological ground beyond syntax and semantics.**

Paper 63 proves that if nontrivial reflexive reality exists, then there must
exist a necessary pre-categorial ontological ground of its actuality. Papers
61–62 cleared all rival candidates (ghosts, syntax, semantics, external,
self-actualizing ledger); Paper 63 establishes the positive existence.

## Key definitions

- `PreCategorial` — ground outside all excluded categories
- `NecessaryGround` — ontological ground that is pre-categorial
- `NontrivialReflexiveRealityExists` — actual ledger that is not self-actualizing

## Key theorems

- `ground_existence_thm` — Theorem 63.2: if nontrivial reflexive reality exists,
  some ground exists
- `alpha_squeeze` — Theorem 63.1: any adequate ground is pre-categorial
- `alpha_theorem` — Theorem 63.3: ∃ α, necessary pre-categorial ground

## Dependencies

- LedgerGround (Paper 62)
- GhostCollapse (Paper 61)
- RealityAsRecursiveIntelligence (Paper 60)
